WEBVTT

00:29.730 --> 00:30.752
Welcome to God Day.

00:31.613 --> 00:33.476
And I pray you do have a God day.

00:34.597 --> 00:38.844
And this is Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church.

00:38.904 --> 00:59.154
And today I want to share from one of the miracles of the Lord in the Bible about how to receive from God, this miracle in Acts chapter three gives us wisdom and some key principles about how we can receive from God.

00:59.650 --> 01:05.476
And so let's have a look at it in Acts chapter three and read the first few verses to start with.

01:06.718 --> 01:10.482
It's about the healing of a layman at the temple gates.

01:11.543 --> 01:17.229
Now Peter and John went up together to the temple at the hour of prayer, the ninth hour.

01:17.269 --> 01:20.492
And that would have been between eight o'clock and nine o'clock in the morning.

01:21.133 --> 01:25.978
And that was a special hour of prayer when the morning sacrifice was offered up.

01:26.599 --> 01:29.362
And so they would often go to the temple there to pray.

01:29.922 --> 01:49.202
if they lived in Jerusalem, and it says, and a certain man, lame from his mother's womb, was carried, whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple, which is called beautiful, probably because the ornamentation of this gate is particularly beautiful.

01:49.762 --> 01:54.346
And he was put there to ask arms from those who entered the temple.

01:54.426 --> 01:58.290
So there'd be lots of people coming and going, going into the temple.

01:58.370 --> 02:04.716
So it was a great place for him to do some begging for money to feed himself.

02:06.097 --> 02:08.720
And then we get into the miracle.

02:08.840 --> 02:10.982
Peter and John are coming.

02:11.282 --> 02:15.166
Now, first of all, let us just notice a kind of contradiction.

02:15.226 --> 02:19.410
Here this man is every day, probably.

02:19.554 --> 02:21.996
at the greatest place on earth, really.

02:22.056 --> 02:24.419
He's at the temple of God.

02:24.959 --> 02:26.601
He's at the beautiful gate.

02:27.742 --> 02:32.987
You know, he's at the holy place where God's presence is the greatest.

02:33.768 --> 02:36.590
And yet, he's lame.

02:37.731 --> 02:38.732
He's lame from birth.

02:39.553 --> 02:44.878
And this is a picture, of course, all of us in a sense are lame from birth.

02:45.699 --> 02:48.722
Being lame means he couldn't walk, he couldn't move.

02:49.218 --> 02:55.507
He couldn't do, you know, he couldn't have a job or do anything like that.

02:56.228 --> 03:04.699
And there's in a spiritual sense, even from birth we are born in sin and we are not able to serve God.

03:04.739 --> 03:10.707
We are not able to walk in the spirit and to do what is right in our own ability.

03:11.609 --> 03:18.418
There are parts of our lives that are lame and we might even be Christians and we dwell

03:18.498 --> 03:25.968
as it were in the house of God, in the Kingdom of God, and yet we might be like this man that parts of our life are lame.

03:26.589 --> 03:46.194
We're not able to have good relationships, or we're not able to function well in our jobs, or in all kinds, you know, we might be good in some areas, but there are other areas where we are lame, and we don't function as we ought to.

03:46.306 --> 03:49.411
We may have inherited that from our birth, as it were.

03:49.972 --> 04:09.202
But the good news of this miracle is that Jesus wants to heal us and to restore us so that we can walk in the will of God, that we can do God's will, that we can fulfill our roles in life as Father, Mother.

04:09.346 --> 04:12.491
and work in our friendships and so on.

04:12.531 --> 04:22.527
So wherever we're lame, this is a message for us because the Lord wants to heal us and restore us, praise God.

04:23.048 --> 04:30.620
So there are certain steps by which we see this man receive his miracle from God.

04:31.782 --> 04:35.708
Step number one, let's read that in verse four.

04:36.069 --> 04:36.690
It says,

04:37.186 --> 04:40.351
and fixing his eyes with him, on him, with John.

04:40.992 --> 04:43.155
Peter said, look at us.

04:44.216 --> 04:45.458
That's how Peter started.

04:46.199 --> 04:54.011
This man was probably just focused, his head was down, just hoping people would drop some money in his cup.

04:54.832 --> 05:02.082
And the first thing was to get his attention in the right place, to get his focus in the right place.

05:02.643 --> 05:04.626
And to look

05:05.058 --> 05:06.985
where the answer is going to come from.

05:07.105 --> 05:10.597
In this case, God was going to do it through Peter and John.

05:11.099 --> 05:13.246
And so he says, look at us.

05:13.949 --> 05:15.093
That's the first thing he does.

05:15.173 --> 05:17.842
He gets them to have the right focus.

05:17.922 --> 05:18.743
to look to God.

05:18.803 --> 05:22.028
You see, many people, they look at their problems.

05:22.048 --> 05:23.650
They look at their circumstances.

05:24.171 --> 05:29.739
But we all need to look at God because God is the source of every good thing.

05:29.759 --> 05:31.702
God is the source of all grace.

05:32.203 --> 05:33.705
The answer is with God.

05:34.046 --> 05:39.374
And so worry is futile because it's just focusing on your problems and your inabilities.

05:40.215 --> 05:42.438
Instead, you need to look to God.

05:43.159 --> 05:45.042
See what you look at determines.

05:46.690 --> 05:47.972
what you're going to receive.

05:49.053 --> 05:55.442
Are you looking at your feelings, your emotions, your problems, or are you looking to God?

05:55.502 --> 05:57.825
The first principle of faith is that God is your source.

05:58.086 --> 06:00.509
You need to look to God, put your trust in God.

06:00.549 --> 06:08.560
And so don't look at medical reports, bank accounts, limitations, problems.

06:09.261 --> 06:12.826
Yes, we're aware of them, but our main focus is on God.

06:13.547 --> 06:14.568
We're looking to God.

06:14.588 --> 06:16.050
And so

06:16.418 --> 06:18.821
God is the source of every good gift.

06:19.422 --> 06:22.406
And to receive from God, you must look to God.

06:22.767 --> 06:24.930
Let's just see a few scriptures on this.

06:25.310 --> 06:31.619
Hebrews 12-2 says, looking unto Jesus, who is the author and the finisher of our faith.

06:32.360 --> 06:39.370
Psalm 34, verse five says, they looked to him and were radiant and their faces were not ashamed.

06:40.271 --> 06:44.817
Isaiah 45, 22, God says, look to me and be saved.

06:44.917 --> 06:45.458
Notice.

06:45.666 --> 06:47.968
Before you be saved, you must look to Him.

06:48.589 --> 06:49.890
Look to Him Me and be saved.

06:50.010 --> 06:53.333
All you ends of the earth, for I am God and there is no other.

06:53.934 --> 06:58.078
So this is the first principle of receiving from God is you must look to Him.

06:58.999 --> 07:04.164
Then the second thing is, it's not just looking to Him, but looking to Him with expectancy.

07:05.085 --> 07:06.927
You see, expect to receive.

07:07.327 --> 07:09.209
So notice verse five.

07:10.370 --> 07:14.354
So this layman gave them his attention.

07:15.042 --> 07:17.926
expecting to receive something from him.

07:18.627 --> 07:21.811
You see this, this was necessary.

07:22.251 --> 07:24.394
He was looking with expectancy.

07:25.215 --> 07:29.401
And so we must also look to God with expectation.

07:30.602 --> 07:39.634
By the way, confident expectation is Bible hope, a confident expectation based on the goodness of God, the character of God.

07:39.714 --> 07:41.877
This is a posture of faith.

07:42.177 --> 07:49.227
We look to God with expectancy because God is good, which means he's generous and he is giving us his grace.

07:50.088 --> 07:55.355
And so this is not hollow, but it's anchored in God's covenant promises.

07:55.435 --> 08:01.142
He promises to be generous, to be gracious to all those who turn to him and look to him.

08:02.364 --> 08:07.090
Hebrews 11, 6 says, for without faith it's impossible to please God.

08:07.522 --> 08:15.935
For he who comes to God must believe that he is and that he is a rewarder of those who diligently seek him.

08:16.756 --> 08:26.771
You see, we have to believe, if we truly believe, we come to him in faith and that involves believing that he's a rewarder of those who diligently seek him.

08:27.372 --> 08:33.361
So we come with expectation that as we seek him, he will bless us, he will reward us.

08:34.303 --> 08:36.466
He says, if you seek me, you'll find me.

08:37.698 --> 08:40.102
We see this in blind Bartimaeus.

08:41.225 --> 08:44.370
He came to Jesus with the expectation of being healed.

08:44.431 --> 08:49.921
In Mark chapter 10, verse 46, it says, now they came to Jericho.

08:50.342 --> 08:59.218
And as he went out of Jericho with his disciples and a great multitude, blind Bartimaeus, the son of Timaeus, came, sat by the road begging.

08:59.970 --> 09:06.276
And when he heard it was Jesus of Nazareth, he began to cry out and say, Jesus, son of David, have mercy on me.

09:06.296 --> 09:08.418
See, he believed that Jesus is the Messiah.

09:08.458 --> 09:12.102
He's the son of David and now have mercy on me.

09:13.543 --> 09:17.647
And many told him to shut up, be quiet, but he cried out all the more.

09:18.267 --> 09:19.809
Son of David, have mercy on me.

09:19.889 --> 09:25.514
Notice he is, his attention is on Jesus and he's calling out to Jesus.

09:26.315 --> 09:29.458
He's looking to Jesus to have mercy on him.

09:30.146 --> 09:35.074
So Jesus stood still and commanded him to be called.

09:35.414 --> 09:39.861
See, when you are calling out to the Lord, Jesus pays attention.

09:40.562 --> 09:47.994
And it says, then they called the blind man saying to him, be of good cheer, rise, he's calling you and throwing aside his garment.

09:48.314 --> 09:52.120
Now that was called the blind man's garment, the beggar's garment.

09:53.402 --> 09:58.290
And by throwing his garment aside, he was showing that he expected to receive.

09:58.722 --> 10:01.005
that he is not going to be a beggar anymore.

10:01.105 --> 10:06.132
He won't need that cloak anymore because that's why he threw aside that garment.

10:06.272 --> 10:08.575
He was expecting to receive.

10:09.456 --> 10:14.523
And he rose and came to Jesus and he answered and said to him, what do you want me to do for you?

10:15.043 --> 10:16.986
So Jesus wanted him to be specific.

10:17.947 --> 10:26.098
And so when we are expectant, then we should be able to clearly articulate

10:26.754 --> 10:36.365
What it is, if it's a burning desire, we should be able to articulate, not just generally bless me, but Lord, I'm asking you, this is what I need.

10:37.386 --> 10:42.472
And so, the blind man said to him, Raboni, that I may receive my sight.

10:43.293 --> 10:46.096
So he is asking Jesus with expectancy.

10:46.817 --> 10:50.140
And Jesus said to him, go your way, your faith has made you well.

10:50.741 --> 10:54.005
And immediately he received this sight and followed Jesus on the road.

10:54.365 --> 10:55.026
Hallelujah.

10:55.554 --> 11:01.683
Well, we see the same kind of expectancy of faith with the woman with the issue of blood in Mark 5.

11:01.723 --> 11:06.771
It says that she had this flow of blood for 12 years, verse 25.

11:06.811 --> 11:10.136
And the doctors couldn't help her.

11:10.357 --> 11:11.278
She just got worse.

11:12.059 --> 11:17.127
And then it says, when she heard about Jesus, she came behind him in the crowd and touched his garment.

11:17.608 --> 11:24.178
And here's the expectancy, verse 28, for she said, if only I may touch his clothes,

11:24.514 --> 11:25.615
I shall be made well."

11:26.196 --> 11:27.477
She heard about Jesus.

11:27.537 --> 11:29.219
She knew he was generous.

11:29.279 --> 11:31.302
He knew he had healing power.

11:32.383 --> 11:32.924
She knew that.

11:33.805 --> 11:39.591
And so she had, she turned to him and came to him and she had expectancy.

11:40.112 --> 11:41.133
I shall be made well.

11:41.754 --> 11:49.863
And immediately it says, the fountain of her blood was dried up and she felt in her body that she was healed of her affliction.

11:50.364 --> 11:52.466
And Jesus said to her in verse 34,

11:53.154 --> 11:55.537
daughter, your faith has made you well.

11:55.557 --> 11:56.137
Praise God.

11:56.958 --> 12:06.328
So Proverbs 23, 18 says, there is surely a hereafter or a latter end and your hope will not be cut off.

12:07.490 --> 12:09.652
You can have hope because God is good.

12:10.132 --> 12:13.176
If you trust in him, he will not let you down.

12:13.716 --> 12:17.961
Proverbs 10, 28, the hope of the righteous will be gladness.

12:18.862 --> 12:21.505
But the expectation of the wicked will perish.

12:22.125 --> 12:22.706
So we

12:22.786 --> 12:32.156
We focus on the Lord and we have expectancy based on his promises that he will be kind and generous to bless us.

12:32.597 --> 12:33.197
Praise God.

12:34.038 --> 12:40.085
And in the third principle we see in Acts chapter three, let's read in verse six.

12:40.105 --> 12:52.658
Then Peter said, silver and gold, I do not have, but what I do have, I give you in the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and walk.

12:53.538 --> 13:01.851
And the next principle is that God's power, God's blessing is in the name of Jesus.

13:02.552 --> 13:11.366
The name of Jesus represents his revealed character, but it also represents all he has done, all he's accomplished for us and all he possesses.

13:11.727 --> 13:13.650
So within the name of Jesus,

13:13.730 --> 13:21.178
is included, everything that Jesus has purchased for us on the cross, that he now possesses as the perfect man.

13:21.258 --> 13:24.602
He, in the resurrection, he received every blessing for us.

13:25.283 --> 13:26.985
And that blessing is in his name.

13:27.625 --> 13:35.955
And if we trust in him, we can call on the name of Jesus and receive salvation and receive blessing and receive healing.

13:36.395 --> 13:42.482
It's all in the name of Jesus because he has himself purchased it and received it from God.

13:42.594 --> 13:46.920
And now we can call on his name and draw from what he has done from us.

13:46.960 --> 13:49.703
So that's why he says in the name of Jesus Christ.

13:49.743 --> 13:52.807
In other words, your healing is in the name of Jesus.

13:52.887 --> 13:55.931
Jesus has accomplished it through his death and resurrection.

13:56.252 --> 13:58.695
It's in his name and he's given us his name.

13:59.336 --> 14:01.979
And so in the name of Jesus, rise up and walk.

14:02.880 --> 14:08.628
And so that's the key is to realize that God's answer, God's power is in the name of Jesus.

14:08.908 --> 14:10.450
It's in Jesus.

14:11.074 --> 14:19.225
And he has given us his name to call on, because it says, all who call on the name of Jesus shall be saved.

14:19.245 --> 14:22.409
And that's what he said later in Acts 3, verse 16.

14:23.150 --> 14:32.562
It says, Peter explaining how the miracle happened, he says, and his name through faith in his name has made this man strong.

14:32.994 --> 14:41.344
whom you see and know, yes, the faith which comes through him has given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.

14:41.364 --> 14:50.235
In other words, he says, it was through the name of Jesus that this man was healed and through faith in his name.

14:50.856 --> 14:57.004
And so that's the next key is to have faith in the name of Jesus that your answer is in the name of Jesus.

14:57.124 --> 15:01.970
It's in Christ, praise God, and you have the ability to

15:02.114 --> 15:07.199
through faith to draw on him by calling on his name.

15:08.140 --> 15:12.225
And it's interesting in Acts 4, 12, when he's still explaining the miracle.

15:12.866 --> 15:21.455
It says, nor is there salvation in any other than Jesus, for there is no other name under heaven given among men by which we must be saved.

15:21.955 --> 15:24.838
In other words, the name of Jesus contains salvation.

15:26.140 --> 15:31.986
Jesus is our Savior and he has purchased and possesses our salvation.

15:32.098 --> 15:40.449
And this name has been given among men so that we can call on the name of Jesus and receive that salvation.

15:41.150 --> 15:47.879
And so the power is in Jesus and it's accessed through the name of Jesus.

15:49.161 --> 15:50.543
Or we could put it like this.

15:51.044 --> 15:57.672
His power is in us because Christ is in us through the Holy Spirit.

15:58.293 --> 16:01.778
And so not only has Jesus got

16:02.146 --> 16:07.213
our salvation, but now that we're saved, the Holy Spirit comes to live in us.

16:07.373 --> 16:09.796
Christ lives in us, praise God.

16:10.196 --> 16:19.669
And so what he has done is already been given to us, and we have the blessing in the Holy Spirit who is in us.

16:20.430 --> 16:28.660
And so as we call on the name of Jesus, we can draw upon his grace and his blessing by faith.

16:29.601 --> 16:30.162
And so

16:30.338 --> 16:36.286
His power is already available to us through His do-normous power within.

16:37.207 --> 16:45.758
And as we believe, that power will be revealed in our life.

16:45.778 --> 16:51.585
And so we are already saved and blessed and anointed and redeemed and blessed.

16:51.906 --> 16:58.354
Ephesians 1.3 says, we've been blessed with every spiritual blessing in Christ.

16:59.042 --> 17:06.754
all these things are in his name and he lives in us and so we can lay hold of these things.

17:07.475 --> 17:10.039
Praise God that he has promised to give us.

17:11.862 --> 17:20.835
And so that's why in Mark 1124 it says, you know, whatsoever things you ask when you pray, believe that you receive them and you will have them.

17:21.376 --> 17:27.826
These are things that are the will of God, of course, things that has been purchased by Jesus through his

17:28.034 --> 17:28.915
death on the cross.

17:29.556 --> 17:30.838
Well, that's the third principle.

17:30.898 --> 17:38.149
Now, the fourth principle is that we can release the power of God by words of faith.

17:38.730 --> 17:40.332
That's what Peter did in verse six.

17:40.372 --> 17:43.757
He said, silver and gold, I don't have, but what I have, I give to you.

17:44.719 --> 17:53.972
You know, he activated this miracle through his words by saying in the name of Jesus, rise up and walk.

17:54.152 --> 17:57.938
And through saying that, in obedience to God, of course,

17:58.114 --> 18:01.517
He released the power of the Spirit that was in the name of Jesus.

18:02.178 --> 18:05.922
The name is the authority and the Holy Spirit is the power.

18:06.802 --> 18:14.009
For example, Acts 1 8 says, you shall receive power when the Holy Spirit has come upon you.

18:14.069 --> 18:18.614
Now this word for power here is dunamis, which really means potential energy.

18:18.974 --> 18:20.536
It's where we get the word dynamite from.

18:20.576 --> 18:25.420
If you see a stick of dynamite, it doesn't look powerful because it's potential energy.

18:25.841 --> 18:27.122
It has to be ignited.

18:27.394 --> 18:29.357
for it for that power to be released.

18:29.657 --> 18:31.319
But it's there in potential form.

18:31.640 --> 18:37.608
So when you've received the Holy Spirit, the power is there in the Holy Spirit and that power is in you and upon you.

18:38.109 --> 18:42.414
But it's dormant until you activate it.

18:42.435 --> 18:44.818
And it says, but it's power to be witnesses.

18:45.318 --> 18:50.866
So he says, the Holy Spirit come upon you and you will be my witnesses to the ends of the earth.

18:51.458 --> 18:52.859
How do you activate that power?

18:52.940 --> 19:08.896
It's by your words when you actually step out, believing that you have the Holy Spirit and that He is upon you, then you believe that as you witness to Jesus, that power will be released and the Holy Spirit will be released once you are obeyed and speak those words.

19:08.916 --> 19:19.026
So in a big way, that power is released by your words and by your actions, by your obedience.

19:19.138 --> 19:27.047
The blessing of God is in you, in the Holy Spirit, and you activate it by your words, as well as your actions.

19:27.087 --> 19:29.990
So that's why it says Proverbs 18, 21.

19:30.250 --> 19:32.373
It says, death and life are in the power of the tongue.

19:33.274 --> 19:35.176
And those who love it will eat its fruit.

19:35.316 --> 19:39.701
In other words, you can release death or life through your tongue.

19:40.401 --> 19:42.664
The blessing of God is voice activated.

19:43.285 --> 19:48.210
God said, let there be light, and then that release the power of God.

19:48.738 --> 19:51.081
of His Spirit to create the universe.

19:51.882 --> 19:56.327
And we can't do that, of course, but we are made in the image of God.

19:57.148 --> 20:04.017
So spiritually, we are able to, as we speak the words of God, we can release the blessing of God.

20:04.958 --> 20:07.541
That allows the Holy Spirit to flow through us.

20:07.841 --> 20:09.944
It's all based on it being the will of God, of course.

20:10.685 --> 20:18.354
But if something's the will of God, by giving our voice and declaring the Word of God, the promise of God,

20:18.434 --> 20:25.966
that allows the Holy Spirit to move freely through us, to bring the will of God to pass.

20:25.986 --> 20:35.882
And so it says in Revelation 12, 11, they overcame Him, the devil, by the blood of the Lamb, and by the word of their testimony, you see.

20:36.543 --> 20:45.778
And Mark 11, 23 says, that whoever says to this mountain, be there removed and be cast into the sea.

20:46.018 --> 20:49.523
He believes that what he says will come to pass, he will have whatever he says.

20:49.723 --> 21:02.021
So again, there is an important place for the fact that we release when we speak the words of God, the words of faith, we actually release God's power.

21:02.883 --> 21:13.458
As Paul says in Romans 10-10, with the heart man believes unto righteousness and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.

21:13.602 --> 21:15.965
Confession means saying the same thing as God.

21:16.806 --> 21:17.867
Speaking God's word.

21:18.407 --> 21:23.673
When we do that, we release the power of God that brings salvation.

21:23.693 --> 21:25.615
Alright, so that's the fourth principle.

21:25.655 --> 21:29.500
Now the fifth principle, obedient action is required.

21:29.600 --> 21:38.650
There comes a point when we receive from God that we need to put our actions to our faith, add actions to our faith.

21:39.130 --> 21:42.514
Verse 7, in Acts chapter 3, it says, and he

21:42.722 --> 21:50.173
Peter took him by the right hand and lifted him up and immediately his feet and ankle bones received strength.

21:50.693 --> 21:53.517
Notice, Peter didn't just speak to him.

21:53.978 --> 21:54.799
He raised him up.

21:55.220 --> 21:56.562
He helped him to get up.

21:56.942 --> 21:59.686
He's helping him to act on his faith.

22:00.307 --> 22:05.234
And it was while he was acting on his faith, that strength came to his ankles.

22:05.858 --> 22:08.641
And then he stood and then he leaped and then he ran.

22:09.121 --> 22:10.903
In other words, there is a gradual process.

22:11.303 --> 22:15.627
But there comes a point where you have to move out of passivity and you have to act.

22:16.588 --> 22:17.449
Do what you can.

22:17.509 --> 22:22.694
And then God's power is released.

22:23.395 --> 22:29.221
As James 1 22 says, be doers of the word, not here as only the saving yourselves.

22:29.921 --> 22:34.706
So there comes a point where God you receive from God and then God

22:34.946 --> 22:40.774
says, okay, you've received, let's say, you've received my power to forgive that person.

22:41.334 --> 22:44.719
But then you have to go ahead and obey God and actually do it.

22:46.401 --> 22:52.929
Or if you're receiving healing from God, he will tell you, well, now try to do something that you couldn't do before.

22:53.250 --> 22:55.152
Take an action, even if it's a small one.

22:55.553 --> 23:00.599
And as you act in faith, the power of God can be released as it was for this man.

23:02.101 --> 23:02.642
And so,

23:04.066 --> 23:07.690
We, we have to overcome somebody lame all their life.

23:07.750 --> 23:09.531
You can imagine they're going to be passive.

23:09.712 --> 23:12.955
They're not, they're going to not do that.

23:13.015 --> 23:17.720
So that he needed to be helped and encouraged to actually take action.

23:18.140 --> 23:27.530
And as he did it, notice his, the power of God flowed and he was fully healed, praise God.

23:27.610 --> 23:31.954
So once you've come to God and received his promise,

23:32.834 --> 23:36.718
then ask, what action can I take to show my faith?

23:37.619 --> 23:40.442
And it's important that we cooperate with God.

23:42.043 --> 23:51.052
You know, as a quick example, in Luke 17, there was a story of 10 lepers in verse 12, and they asked Jesus to have mercy on them.

23:51.713 --> 23:55.697
And in verse 14, he said to them, go show yourself to the priests.

23:56.898 --> 23:59.000
In other words, take action, act on your faith.

24:00.121 --> 24:01.042
And it says that,

24:01.218 --> 24:03.320
As they went, they were cleansed.

24:03.340 --> 24:06.684
They had to believe His promise that He was healing them.

24:07.305 --> 24:09.827
And as they went, they were cleansed.

24:09.927 --> 24:15.353
So as they took action in obedience, then the power of God was released.

24:17.115 --> 24:24.043
We don't have time for it, but in 2 Kings 7, 3 to 8, there's a story of four lepers at the gate.

24:24.623 --> 24:26.886
And there was a famine throughout the city.

24:27.567 --> 24:30.610
And, you know, they decided

24:31.106 --> 24:33.889
rather than just waiting there to die.

24:33.949 --> 24:37.833
They said, well, let's go to the Syrian camp.

24:38.613 --> 24:39.955
And they took action.

24:40.255 --> 24:45.420
Verse five says, and they rose at twilight to go to the camp of the Syrians.

24:45.841 --> 24:51.126
And when they'd come to the outskirts of the Syrian camp, to their surprise, no one was there.

24:51.847 --> 24:57.813
For the Lord had caused the army of the Syrians to hear the noise of the chariots and the noise of the horses of a great army.

24:57.853 --> 24:59.154
And they said to each other,

24:59.298 --> 25:04.343
Look, the king of Israel is hired against us, the kings of the Hittites and the kings of the Egyptians to attack us.

25:04.643 --> 25:09.007
Therefore, they arose and fled at twilight and left the camp intact.

25:09.347 --> 25:15.373
And when the lepers arrived, they found all the food and that left there that they could enjoy the spoils.

25:16.194 --> 25:20.498
But notice, when did the lepers start their march on the enemy camp?

25:20.818 --> 25:21.659
When did they act?

25:22.220 --> 25:29.106
They were acting on a prophecy of Elijah who said, within 24 hours, everyone's going to be free.

25:29.410 --> 25:35.095
And so they took action and they left at twilight, it says.

25:36.537 --> 25:37.818
And when did the enemy flee?

25:38.299 --> 25:41.982
The enemy fled at twilight because they heard the sound of a mighty army.

25:42.423 --> 25:48.428
Actually, it was the army of the Lord that was making the angelic army of the Lord.

25:48.809 --> 25:58.578
So the moment they marched at twilight, God's power was released and the army of the Lord marched with them.

25:59.074 --> 26:02.799
and the sound of the army of the Lord caused the enemy to flee at twilight.

26:02.859 --> 26:06.384
So notice the power was released through their action.

26:06.765 --> 26:14.436
And then just finally, the final principle is that having received from God, then praise and thank God.

26:15.357 --> 26:18.501
That's what happened in Acts three, verse eight.

26:18.802 --> 26:23.869
So leaping up, he stood and walked and entered the temple with them, walking, leaping and praising God.

26:24.610 --> 26:27.634
And all the people saw him walking and praising God.

26:28.482 --> 26:29.203
Praise God.

26:29.583 --> 26:30.904
And so that is the right thing.

26:31.325 --> 26:32.165
Keep praising God.

26:32.246 --> 26:39.512
Keep thanking God because that keeps your focus on God so that his power and his blessing can continue to flow.

26:39.532 --> 26:42.715
It opens the door for more and more of God's blessing.

26:43.396 --> 26:58.130
And going back to the story of those lepers in Luke chapter 17, there was one of those 10 who when he saw he was healed, he went back to Jesus and he gave him thanks.

26:58.914 --> 27:01.577
And Jesus said, where are the other nine?

27:02.278 --> 27:04.580
But he was the only one who gave thanks.

27:04.821 --> 27:06.062
He gave glory to God.

27:06.583 --> 27:12.049
And verse 19, he said to him, arise, go your way, your faith has made you well.

27:12.529 --> 27:27.506
And what I believe this means is he wasn't just cleansed of the leprosy that any of the rotting flesh was now cleansed and healed, but now fingers and a hand, let's say anything part of his body that he lost through this

27:27.618 --> 27:31.042
Leprosy, now it says, your faith has made you whole.

27:31.383 --> 27:36.248
In other words, he received full restoration of what he had lost.

27:36.809 --> 27:39.793
Whereas the others, they received their cleansing, yes.

27:40.454 --> 27:43.878
But the process wasn't complete because they didn't give thanks to God.

27:44.138 --> 27:57.234
But when you continue to give thanks to God for what he's done for you, then his power can keep flowing and he can not only cleanse you of the past, but also he can restore what everything that has been lost.

27:57.538 --> 28:03.124
That's important as well that we know to cleanse God.

28:03.164 --> 28:06.128
So remember these principles to receive from God.

28:06.508 --> 28:07.910
Put your attention on God.

28:08.250 --> 28:10.693
Expect to receive from Him.

28:11.294 --> 28:17.381
And remember that everything you need is in the name of Jesus and that you can call on the name of Jesus.

28:18.202 --> 28:25.490
And the power of the Holy Spirit can be released even from the inside of you because it's all in Christ.

28:25.602 --> 28:28.586
and Christ is in you, praise God.

28:29.086 --> 28:38.117
And you can declare and release the blessing of God by speaking God's words and God's promises.

28:38.778 --> 28:45.246
And remember, when it's time to take action, act, put action to your faith.

28:46.027 --> 28:53.817
Whatever you can do, put action to your faith and that will help you cooperate with God to release the power of God.

28:53.857 --> 28:54.898
And then of course,

28:55.106 --> 28:56.088
Give Him thanks.

28:56.889 --> 28:57.530
Give Him thanks.

28:58.211 --> 29:01.437
And don't wait for the full manifestation before you give Him thanks.

29:01.497 --> 29:02.318
Just give Him thanks.

29:02.799 --> 29:06.405
And that will keep the power and the blessing of God flowing.

29:07.186 --> 29:08.488
So praise God.

29:08.929 --> 29:15.761
We thank God that the layman is, these miracles are given, that we might know how to receive from God.

29:15.801 --> 29:19.026
Amen.

